description:
Roles & Responsibilities
- Provide operation and administration support on system infrastructure according to the agreed service levels
- minimum 3 years in Microsoft Server administration
- Microsoft Certified Solutions Associate (MCSA)
- Singaporean (able to clear CAT 1)

Job Responsibilities:
(a) System administration;
(b) Backup and recovery administration;
(c) Server security administration;
(d) Performance and fault management;
(e) Report requirements; and
(f) Server management support.

Type of system infrastructure includes:
(a) Physical Servers;
(b) Virtual Machines (VMware, Hyper-V, Cloud);
(c) Windows Active Directory (AD, DNS, DHCP, GPO);
(d) Storage (SAN, NAS);
(e) Backup (Veritas, Backup-exec, backup appliance).

Type of Operating System includes:
(a) Windows Server 2012 R2 and later versions of Windows;
(b) Windows Server 2016.

Roles & Responsibilities
Job Duties:

The activities required to be performed shall include the following:
Provision of support for SharePoint farm for enterprise wide implementation;
Provision of technical and operation support to SharePoint developers and users;
Monitoring of services to ensure service availability;
Application of software and security patches;
Incident and problem management;
Development and implementation of operational procedures to improve services;
Project implementation and vendor management.

Job Requirements:

The qualification and work experience required are as follows:
Recognised qualification in Computer Science/Computer Engineering or a relevant discipline;
Minimum 2 years of hands-on experience with the administration of SharePoint infrastructure on-prem, sharePoint Online and OneDrive in Microsoft 365;
Experience with supporting other products in Microsoft 365 will be an added advantage. These include Exchange Online, Teams and Power Platform.
Able to multi-task and work independently, a good team player and possesses good analytical, interpersonal and written communication skills;
SharePoint certification is preferred.

Interested candidates may apply to patrina@eps.com.sg with your detailed CV, stating your expected salary and availability.

Roles & Responsibilities
Job Duties:

The activities required to be performed shall include the following:
Planning, deployment and support of campus-wide communication and collaboration services;
Provision of subject matter expert advice on the most appropriate Unified Communications and Collaboration technologies to deploy to meet business needs;
Working closely with vendors, users and peers to plan, develop and implement appropriate business solutions using either on premise or cloud solutions and following established project management best practices;
Performing day-to-day system delivery and support services, following ITIL best practices, which includes establishing and meeting agreed service levels/standards for service requests, incident & problem resolution, change control, capacity & performance monitoring, systems administration and software patches/update;
Development and implementation of operational procedures to continuously improve the productivity and effectiveness of the services delivered, meeting ISO9000 quality standards.

Job Requirements:
The qualification and work experience required are as follows:
Recognised qualification in Computer Science/Computer Engineering or a relevant discipline;
Minimum 2 years’ relevant experience in delivering and supporting Unified Communication and Collaboration (UCC) services, in particular Exchange Online and MS Teams in Microsoft 365;
Experience with supporting voice gateway, call center and SMS.
Knowledge in Power Platform in Microsoft 365 will be an added advantage.
Able to multi-task and work independently, a good team player and possesses good analytical, interpersonal and written communication skills.

Interested applicants may apply with detailed CV and email to patrina@eps.com.sg , stating your expected salary and availability.

Roles & Responsibilities
Location: Singapore
NextLabs® is the leading provider of policy-driven information risk management (IRM) software for large enterprises, Our customers include many prominent enterprises in Aerospace & Defense, Financial Services, and High-Tech Manufacturing and Engineering industries. NextLabs’ flagship data protection and entitlement management products, Enterprise Data Protection and Compliant Enterprise®, combine with the CloudAz XACML-based policy management platform with integrated content aware and identity-driven enforcement technology to offer the most comprehensive information risk management (IRM) solution. Our products preserve confidentiality, prevent data loss, and ensure compliance across more channels and more points, within a single unified solution with the unmatched user acceptance and Total Cost of Ownership (TCO).
The IT System Administrator will be responsible to provide consistent network and computer system administration, to include: implementation, technical assistance, customer service and support; training and guidance; communications; desktop, servers, Internet/Intranet, software and related security.
Responsibilities:
To Lead / Co-lead in planning and implementing, developing, testing and support the IT application and systems for head office and all branches;
Administer, maintain and support internal and cloud infrastructure consisting of Windows Active Directory spanning across the US and South East Asia Region;
Focus on and responsible for troubleshooting support to include; software, network, server, and workstation problem resolutions and support for upgrades and patches;
Monitoring, reporting and troubleshooting of all assigned equipment, systems, applications, and all associated systems;
Performs preventative maintenance and manage problem resolution and upgrades;
To provide first level technical support for End Users to ensure business continuity.
Escalate and route calls and tickets to different level support per defined processes;
Provide 24/7 support and resolution on critical production issue, and problems;
To enforce security policies and standards;
Responsible for technical documentation of the IT systems;
Develop training materials and procedures to train users in the proper use of hardware and software and instruction for system users on operating systems, relational databases, and other applications; assist users in maximizing use of networks and computing systems to ensure consistency in all office locations;
Conduct various training as required on supported systems, equipment, and applications;
Vendor management: Negotiate and administer vendor, outsourcer and consultant contracts and service agreements;
Provide customer and personal service to end user in multiple locations. This includes customer needs assessment, meeting quality standards for services, and evaluation of customer satisfaction
Requirements:
At least 3 year(s) of working experience in the related field is required for this System Administration position.
Experience with Microsoft technologies in a multi-site environment including AD/Exchange server replication
Required skill(s): Microsoft Active Directory, TCP/IP, VMware/Microsoft Hyper-V
Candidate must possess at least a Professional Certificate, Bachelor’s Degree, Post Graduate Diploma, Professional Degree, Computer Science/Information Technology, Engineering (Computer/Telecommunication) or equivalent.
Proficient in English Speaking, writing and reading.
Experience with Service-now or other ITIL products a plus
Experience in support Linux environment is preferable
Experience in CI/CD (Jenkins/Hudson/GIT) is a preferable
Ability to create scripts in Python, Perl or other language
Ability to prioritize and multi-task in a fast-paced and dynamic environment
Positive attitude – goes the extra mile, is committed, willing to take on challenges and has a can-do mind-set.
Ability to take ownership of projects and follow through to completion and yet be able to work as part of a team
A sense of urgency in getting the job done. May need to work extra hours and weekends when needed
Team focused – looks to the success of the whole rather than the self and see the ‘bigger picture’
Desire to learn new skills
Self-motivated and goal oriented
Excellent verbal and written communication skills
Interested candidates may send resume to jobs.sg@nextlabs.com
